30namespace OneD {

32MultiUPCEANReader::MultiUPCEANReader(const DecodeHints& hints)
33{
34 _canReturnUPCA = hints.hasNoFormat() || hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::UPC_A);
35 DecodeHints _hints = hints;
36 if (_hints.hasNoFormat()) {
37 _hints.setFormats(BarcodeFormat::EAN_13 | BarcodeFormat::EAN_8 | BarcodeFormat::UPC_E);
38 // UPC-A is covered by EAN-13
39 }
40
41 if (_hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::EAN_13)) {
42 _readers.emplace_back(new EAN13Reader(hints));
43 }
44 else if (_hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::UPC_A)) {
45 _readers.emplace_back(new UPCAReader(hints));
46 }
47 if (_hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::EAN_8)) {
48 _readers.emplace_back(new EAN8Reader(hints));
49 }
50 if (_hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::UPC_E)) {
51 _readers.emplace_back(new UPCEReader(hints));
52 }
53}
54
55MultiUPCEANReader::~MultiUPCEANReader() = default;
56
57Result
58MultiUPCEANReader::decodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState>&) const
59{
60 // Compute this location once and reuse it on multiple implementations
61 auto range = UPCEANReader::FindStartGuardPattern(row);
62 if (!range)
63 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
64
65 for (auto& reader : _readers) {
66 Result result = reader->decodeRow(rowNumber, row, range);
67 if (!result.isValid())
68 continue;
69
70 // Special case: a 12-digit code encoded in UPC-A is identical to a "0"
71 // followed by those 12 digits encoded as EAN-13. Each will recognize such a code,
72 // UPC-A as a 12-digit string and EAN-13 as a 13-digit string starting with "0".
73 // Individually these are correct and their readers will both read such a code
74 // and correctly call it EAN-13, or UPC-A, respectively.
75 //
76 // In this case, if we've been looking for both types, we'd like to call it
77 // a UPC-A code. But for efficiency we only run the EAN-13 decoder to also read
78 // UPC-A. So we special case it here, and convert an EAN-13 result to a UPC-A
79 // result if appropriate.
80 //
81 // But, don't return UPC-A if UPC-A was not a requested format!
82 const std::wstring& resultText = result.text();
83 bool ean13MayBeUPCA = result.format() == BarcodeFormat::EAN_13 && !resultText.empty() && resultText[0] == '0';
84 if (ean13MayBeUPCA && _canReturnUPCA) {
85 result.setText(resultText.substr(1));
86 result.setFormat(BarcodeFormat::UPC_A);
87 }
88 return result;
89 }
90 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
91}
